      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm stuck on this coding assignment for my algorithms class. i need to write a function that finds the longest palindromic substring in a huge string, but my current code is super slow. the autograder at my uni is really strict about the time limit—if it takes more than a second for a string with 100,000 characters it just fails me. \n\ncan you help me optimize this? i really just need it to pass the runtime check for those massive inputs.\n\nhere is my current code:\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    n = len(s)\n    res = \"\"\n    for i in range(n):\n        for j in range(i, n):\n            sub = s[i:j+1]\n            if sub == sub[::-1] and len(sub) > len(res):\n                res = sub\n    return res\n```",
